             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a watchman, I saw a cart stop facing Moor Place, and the prisoner Burdett talking to the driver.</p>
               <p>Court. There is not the least evidence against the prisoners.</p>
               <p>BOTH <rs id="t17840707-91-verdict452" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17840707-91-verdict452" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Court to Burdett. Your conduct has been very suspicious indeed, and you have had a very narrow escape because the evidence was defective, I hope you will take care and amend your conduct.</p>
               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. Justice HEATH.</p>
